details.body:
I think the key point here is to get rid of usage of `Azure.ResourceManager.ProxyResource` so that TCGC won't have duplicate `ProxyResource`s.

So current usage:
```typespec
model ApplicationResource
  is Azure.ResourceManager.ProxyResource<ApplicationResourceProperties> {}

@armResourceOperations(#{ omitTags: true })
interface ApplicationResources {
  get is ArmResourceRead<ApplicationResource, Error = ErrorModel>;
}
```

should be replaced by 
```typespec
model ApplicationResource extends Prox

The commented example response uses a pointer for an embedded (non-pointer) response field (e.g., `ClusterCodeVersionsListResult: &armservicefabric.ClusterCodeVersionsListResult{...}`). In `responses.go`, `ClusterVersionsClientGetResponse` embeds `ClusterCodeVersionsListResult` as a value, so the example shape should use a non-pointer composite literal to match the actual type.
```suggestion
	// 	ClusterCodeVersionsListResult: armservicefabric.ClusterCodeVersionsListResult{
```

The commented response example uses `ApplicationTypeResource: &armservicefabric.ApplicationTypeResource{...}`, but `ApplicationTypesClientCreateOrUpdateResponse` embeds `ApplicationTypeResource` as a value in `responses.go`. Adjust the example's commented response shape to use a non-pointer composite literal so it matches the real response type.
```suggestion
	// 	ApplicationTypeResource: armservicefabric.ApplicationTypeResource{
```

The commented response example uses `ApplicationTypeVersionResource: &armservicefabric.ApplicationTypeVersionResource{...}`, but `ApplicationTypeVersionsClientGetResponse` embeds `ApplicationTypeVersionResource` as a value in `responses.go`. Update the commented example response shape to match the actual (non-pointer) field type.
```suggestion
	// 	ApplicationTypeVersionResource: armservicefabric.ApplicationTypeVersionResource{
```

The commented response example uses `ApplicationResource: &armservicefabric.ApplicationResource{...}`, but `ApplicationsClientGetResponse` embeds `ApplicationResource` as a value in `responses.go`. Please update the commented response shape to use a non-pointer composite literal so it matches the real response type.
```suggestion
	// 	ApplicationResource: armservicefabric.ApplicationResource{
```

The commented response example uses `Cluster: &armservicefabric.Cluster{...}`, but `ClustersClientCreateOrUpdateResponse` embeds `Cluster` as a value in `responses.go`. Update the commented example response shape to match the actual (non-pointer) field type to avoid misleading users.
```suggestion
	// 	Cluster: armservicefabric.Cluster{
```
